nl_query: For patients with alkaliphophatase (ALP) within normal range, were they treated as inpatient or outpatient? alkaliphophatase (ALP) within normal range refers to ALP < 300; inpatient refers to admission = '+'; outpatient refers to admission = '-'
golden_query: SELECT T1.Admission FROM Patient AS T1 INNER JOIN Laboratory AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T2.ALP < 300
sparksql_query: SELECT T2.Admission, COUNT(T2.Admission) FROM laboratory AS T1 JOIN patient AS T2 ON T1.ID = T2.ID WHERE T1.ALP < 300 GROUP BY T2.Admission
